The following instructions should be used to add the MAC Address file to the recorder.

1) Create a file with the name "macaddress.txt". Make sure the filename is all lower case.
2) The contents of the file is 6 HEX digits seperated by :. So it would look like XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX
3) To copy this file to the recorder perform the following steps.
	a) Get to the Linux prompt. If m2300 is running, type in ..exit.
	b) Perform the following command - cd /tmp
	c) Use lrz to download the file to the recorder.
	d) When the file is on the recorder perform the following command - cp macaddress /usr/calculex
	e) Perform the following command - sync
4) Cycle power on the recorder